This FN Five-seven pistol is in great condition, fired <150 rounds thru; rarely carried, this pistol is near new in the box with all accessories, and a total of SIX high capacity 20-RD magazines plus 250 rounds of 5.7x28 40 grain VMax ammo. Zero holster wear - no holster. Comes as a package ready to go with original box, papers, org. test-shot cartridge, tools, and six (6) 20-round magazines. One sealed box of 50 cartridges (Ball-SS192) plus 20 rounds and two Kydex holsters included.

The Five-seven is extremely lightweight for a full-size gun, weighing ~ 1.5 lbs with a fully-loaded 20-round magazine and one in the chamber... that's twenty-one rounds; and yet two 20-round mags to go. The Five-seven launches a 40 grain bullet with a screaming super-accurate Muzzle Velocity of 2,350 fps and a Muzzle Energy of 390 ft. lbs. Not bad for a gun that has a kick that feels like a little cricket in your palm, and way, way, fun to shoot.

As stated, in addition to the ammo, two high-quality Kydex holsters are included. Both great for concealed carry: 1) Blade-Tech Inside-the-Waistband (IWB) Holster with pair of IWB snap loops, and two J-hooks (1.25" & 1.5") sets; 2) Fobus Evolution Roto-Holster™ Paddle, rotates 360° employing a forward or rearward cant.

The Five-seven is a full-size pistol, having an overall length of 208 mm (8.2 in), a height of 137 mm (5.4 in), and a max width of 36 mm (1.4 in). It has the same grip angle as the distinguished Browning Hi-Power and M1911 pistols. The Five-seven barrel is cold hammer-forged and chrome-lined, with a total length of 122 mm (4.8 in) and a rifled length of 94 mm (3.7 in). The barrel has eight rifling grooves with a right-hand twist rate of 1:231 mm (1:9.1 in), and it weighs 113 g (0.25 lb). It has a stated service life of 20,000 rounds and the Five-seven is noted for being very accurate.

Current models of the Five-seven are single-action, having a short and light trigger pull of 2 to 3 daN (4.4 to 6.6 lbF). They have a Picatinny rail for mounting accessories, and a magazine safety mechanism that prevents the pistol from firing without a magazine inserted.

postcontent:
"A well-regulated militia, being necessary to the security of a free state, the right of the people to keep and bear arms shall not be infringed." - James Madison

CTLM is located in the Winsted area. We are looking for any and all Patriots, Preppers, Constitutionalists, etc.  
We meet 2-4 times a month where we either conduct a meeting or training exercises. Because we are currently not at war we do group recreational/teambuilding activites such as fishing, hiking, survivalist activities, wilderness exploration, camp craft, first aid, shooting range days and many other activities such as long term bugging in and self reliance. 
CTLM so far consists of preppers, patriots, Minutemen, and outdoorsmen. We are all like-minded and you should be also if you wish to join. We do train with firearms and if you are not familiar with firearms we would be more than willing to teach you how to safely and properly operate and care for your firearm(s). We do have a field dress requirementas well as basic requirements for gear, attendance/participation and other things but the dress code does not apply to standard meetings. 
If you are looking for a NWO anti-government radical group, or some Anarchist regmine turn away now. We do not want you nor require your presence.
We do want LEGAL citizens who:
-Do NOT have a criminal record.
-support the United States Constitution and the Bill of Rights.
- believe in and cherish indivdual freedom 
-understand and agree that the Founding Fathers believed that all free men have the right to life, liberty and the pursuit of happiness.
-The right to keep and bare arms shall not be infringed
-The government can "save all of us" from any major catastrophe, disaster or attack.

We are a not extremists or right wing radicals. We are law abiding Americans who believe that there is a need for an organized group to protect and preserve Freedom, Liberty and America. The government cannot help us all, look at incidents like Katrina or even Hurricane Sandy. It is our moral duty to ensure that when SHTF we are there for our families, friends, communities and country. We are average working residents who live among you, but we are trained and we will train you to be able to help your fellow citizens, your community and fight for your freedom and way of life (when necissary) in situations like:
Domestic or foreign terror attacks, natural disasters, industrial disasters, unlawful intrusion of an invading army, Economic collapse, riots, civil disorder/chaos.

Many of us are law abiding firearm owners but we are NOT militants or combatants. If you have special skills or training from working as an EMT, military service, etc we would love for you to join. 
**MEMBERS WHO HAVE SERVED IN THE MILITARY AND SEEN ACTION WILL BE PRIORITY ASSIGNED TO CTLM's COMMAND AUTHORITY. WE CURRENTLY HAVE 3 SLOTS OPEN** 
UPDATE: We are urgently seeking Patriots who meet the following criteria:
-Vehicle and small engine Mechanic (prefer someone ASE certified)
- Machinist familar with CNC, mill drills etc.
-5acres+ of private land.
-Computer guy/tech (web design, graphics)
-Military servicemen/women who achieved E-4 to W-1 rank. (MUST NOT BE ACTIVE DUTY! Sorry, I just don't want to endanger your Military standing or create any conflicts that could harm your reputation or anything. Once something is in black and white and put in a file, its never going to go away). 
If you would like more information please email me, Dave at the email provided.
Our next meeting time and place has yet to be scheduled and we are currently in our infancy in respects to establishment. We will not hold a formal meeting until we have atleast 10 members or people "signed up."

I believe everyone has the right to be prepared for whatever Nature or the gov't can throw at us. If that means being armed with anything from  a gun to a fire extinguisher, a generator or a "doomsday bunker" than that is how it needs to be.

In Liberty, Molon Labe. God Bless
Thanks.

title: For Sale:  COLT LE CARBINE LE6940 AR15 5.56MM
postcontent: Description: Up for auction is a factory new in box Colt LE6940 rifle. Introduced in 2009, the Colt LE6940 Advanced Law Enforcement Carbine is best thought of as a semi-automatic-only version of the M4 modified with Colt’s proprietary monolithic one-piece upper receiver and handguard. This upper receiver traces its origins back some six years to guns Colt produced for the SCAR (Special Operations Forces Combat Assault Rifle) program of the U.S. Special Operations Command (SOCOM). It is designed to obviate the need for a separate multiple-rail handguard for mounting accessories, affording perfect alignment of accessories mounted in-line with the primary optical device, providing extreme rigidity, and allowing the removal and reinstallation of optics without loss of zero. Additionally, the handguard section provides sufficient ventilation to prevent heat buildup around the barrel. And the monolithic upper weighs less than a standard upper receiver with separate quad-rail handguard attached. The upper, made from a CNC-machined 7075-T6 aluminum forging, features integral top and side Picatinny rails extending forward just to the rear of the gas block. Recesses for quick-detachable sling swivels are located on both side rails. The bottom rail is a separate piece that can be detached for cleaning or installation of under-barrel accessories. All rail sections have numbered slots for repeatable installation of devices. The LE6940 has extensive parts commonality with the M4, sharing the barrel’s chrome-lining, four-position collapsible stock, and birdcage-style flash hider. Also present are the familiar shell deflector, ejection port cover and forward assist. The LE6940’s bolt, carrier and trigger mechanism also follow the proven AR-15 pattern, as do the controls on the lower receiver: magazine release, reversible safety and bolt release. Like all current Colt-produced rifles, the LE6940 uses 0.154-inch-diameter hammer and trigger pins. The 1:7-inch twist of the barrel and 5.56x45 mm NATO chamber allow the use of 55-grain, 62-grain and 77-grain ammunition. The M4-style barrel measures 0.750 inches at the gas block, but decreases to 0.640 inches under the handguard, and incorporates the M4-style step. Barrel attachment is by way of an improved barrel nut that reportedly offers greater strength. Specifications: Action: Semi-Automatic Caliber: 223 Remington/5.56 NATO Bbl Length: 16.1" Capacity: 30+1 Trigger: Direct Safety: Lever OAL: 35.25" Weight: 6.6 lbs Stock: 4-Position Collapsible Finish: Black

title: For Sale:  DANIEL DEFENSE DDMAV5 300 BLACKOUT AR15
postcontent:
Daniel Defense’s 300 Blackout, was originally designed to give the shooter a 30 caliber projectile which could be fired out of the AR platform without an increase in magazine size while still utilizing a standard bolt. The 300 Blackout is 7.62x35mm which gives the shooter similar ballistic qualities as the .308 and the 7.62x39mm, the AK round, without having to give up the light weight 5.56mm/AR platform. The 300 Blackout can still utilize standard AR magazines without a reduction in magazine capacity. Unlike the 7.62x39mm, the 300 Blackout cartridge is still light on the shoulder with similar recoil to the 5.56mm. The 300 Blackout is designed to be shot suppressed and un-surpressed utilizing various type of super sonic and sub sonic ammunitions. The testing of the Daniel Defense 300 BlackOut firearms indicates that un-surpressed firing with sub-sonic ammo can lead to failures to feed, failures, to eject, and failures to fire and is not recommend.

The Uberti Top Break is true to the original, designed by Major George Schofield at the Smith & Wesson factory in 1869. The Schofield revolver was created as a cavalry pistol. Its efficient, break-open design could be operated one-handed. That made it easy to eject all six spent cartridges and reload the single action revolver while on horseback.

The U.S. Cavalry was slow to see the merits of the top break, but Jessie James, John Wesley Hardin, and Wild Bill Hickok saw the fast reloading capability as a distinct advantage in their line of work. After numerous trials, the U.S. Army finally purchased three thousand top breaks with an improved top latch design.

However, it was the Russian government that truly embraced the new sidearm. The Czar ordered 41,000 top breaks with a modified grip design, lanyard ring, and a distinctive trigger spur.
